ISUIElement.notes: **ISUIElement** is the base UI class in the **Project Zomboid** Lua codebase.

IDMax.notes: The next ID to use for a new ISUIElement instance.

anchorBottom.notes: If true, the element is anchored to the bottom of its parent element.

anchorLeft.notes: If true, the element is anchored to the left of its parent element.

anchorRight.notes: If true, the element is anchored to the right of its parent element.

anchorTop.notes: If true, the element is anchored to the top of its parent element.

children.notes: The registered child elements of the element, registered using self.ID as their key.

enabled.notes: If true, the element is active.

forceCursorVisible.notes: If true, the cursor will stay visible when inside the element's box-boundary.

height.notes: The height of the UI element. (In pixels)

ID.notes: The internal ID of the UI element. This is used to store elements in their parent-element's children array.

javaObject.notes: The Java instance of the UI element. This is used to communicate with the game's UI engine.

keepOnScreen.notes: If true, the element will stay on the screen regardless of its state.

minimumHeight.notes: The minimum height of the UI element. (In pixels)

minimumWidth.notes: The minimum width of the UI element. (In pixels)

onMouseDoubleClick.notes: A callback function for double clicking.

parent.notes: If not nil, the parent of the element will be stored here.

removed.notes: True if the UI element is flagged for removal from the UI manager.

scrollwidth.notes: The set scroll-width of the element's scroll pane.

visibleFunction.notes: An optional function to be invoked when self.setVisible() is invoked. Passes two ISUIElements as parameters.

visibleTarget.notes: The element-target or reference to self.visibleFunction when the visibility of the element is changed.

wantKeyEvents.notes: If true, keyboard-events are broadcasted to the element.

width.notes: The width of the UI element. (In pixels)

x.notes: The x coordinate on the screen. (In pixels)

y.notes: The y coordinate on the screen. (In pixels)

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The x coordinate on the screen. (In pixels)

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The y coordinate on the screen. (In pixels)

parameters.name: width
parameters.notes: The width of the UI element. (In pixels)

parameters.name: height
parameters.notes: The height of the UI element. (In pixels)

returns.notes: A formally-wrapped for **tostring(self)** using the** getUIName()** to formally name the printed result.

addChild.notes: Adds a child UI element to this UI element.

parameters.name: other
parameters.notes: The UI element to add as a child to this UI element.

addScrollBars.notes: Adds a vertical ISScrollBar to the UI element.

parameters.name: addHorizontal
parameters.notes: If true, the ISUIElement will also have a horizontal scrollbar.

addToUIManager.notes: Adds this UI element to the UI manager for the game.

backMost.notes: Moves the element to the back-most drawn on the stack of elements to render.

bringToTop.notes: Brings the element to the top of the rendering stack.

clampStencilRectToParent.notes: If the element has a parent, set the stencil box-boundary of the element to its parent.

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The left-most x-coordinate. (In pixels)

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The top-most y-coordinate. (In pixels)

parameters.name: width
parameters.notes: The width of the stencil. (In pixels)

parameters.name: height
parameters.notes: The height of the stencil. (In pixels)

returns.notes: x, y, width, height

clearChildren.notes: Clears all registered child-elements from the element.

clearMaxDrawHeight.notes: Clears the maximum draw height of the element.

clearMaxDrawWidth.notes: Clears the maximum draw width of the element.

clearStencilRect.notes: Clears the set box-boundary for the element.

containsPoint.notes: Tests if the given coordinates are inside the element's box-boundary.

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The x-coordinate to test. (In pixels)

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The y-coordinate to test. (In pixels)

returns.notes: True if the coordinates are inside the element's box-boundary.

containsPointLocal.notes: Tests if the given coordinates are inside the element's local box-boundary. (the top-left of the element is 0,0)

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The x-coordinate to test. (In pixels)

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The y-coordinate to test. (In pixels)

returns.notes: True if the coordinates are inside the element's local box-boundary.

createChildren.notes: Fired when the element is instantiated. Create initial child elements here.

prerender.notes: Triggered before rendering the element. All render-based calculations go here.

removeChild.notes: Removes a child from the element.

parameters.name: child
parameters.notes: The child to remove.

removeFromUIManager.notes: Removes the element reference from the UIManager instance.

render.notes: Triggered when rendering the element. All render calls go here.\n**NOTE**: This is called in the game's render thread. All render calls fired outside of this call are ignored.

repaintStencilRect.notes: Repaints the stencil at the given box-boundary.

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The left-most x-coordinate of the stencil. (In pixels)

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The top-most y-coordinate of the stencil. (In pixels)

parameters.name: width
parameters.notes: The width of the stencil. (In pixels)

parameters.name: height
parameters.notes: The height of the stencil. (In pixels)

resumeStencil.notes: Resumes (or starts) the stencil for the set box boundary of the element. Anything drawn through or outside the box boundaries of the element is clipped & stenciled out of the frame buffer.

setAlwaysOnTop.notes: Sets the element to render at the top of any stack of elements.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: If true, the element anchors to the bottom its parent element.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: If true, the element anchors to the left-side of its parent element.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: If true, the element anchors to the right-side of its parent element.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: If true, the element anchors to the top of its parent element.

setCapture.notes: (Something to do with mouse input capturing)

setController.notes: Sets the controller object for the element.

parameters.name: controller
parameters.notes: The controller object.

setEnabled.notes: Sets the enabled-state of the element. If disabled, the element will not update or render either itself or its children.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setFollowGameWorld.notes: Sets the element's flag for following the game's world offset when the player moves their camera.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setForceCursorVisible.notes: Sets whether the cursor is forced to render if over the element.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setHeight.notes: Sets the height of the element on the screen. (In pixels)\n**NOTE**: If the element is set to stay on the screen, the height is capped.

parameters.name: height
parameters.notes: The height to set. (In pixels)

setHeightAndParentHeight.notes: Sets the height of the element and all parent elements up to their root element. (In pixels)

parameters.name: height
parameters.notes: The height to set. (In pixels)

setMaxDrawHeight.notes: Sets the maximum height the element will draw anything.

parameters.name: height

parameters.notes: The height to set. (In pixels)

parameters.name: target

parameters.notes: The callback to trigger on the MouseEvent.

setRemoved.notes: Sets the element flagged for removal on the next update tick.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setRenderThisPlayerOnly.notes: Sets the player's index that should only be rendered. (-1 if unset)

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The player's index to set. (0 - 3)

setScrollChildren.notes: Sets whether the children of the element should be scrolled.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setScrollWidth.notes: Sets the width of the scrollbar pane.

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The value to set. (In pixels)

parameters.notes: The flag to set.

parameters.name: x

parameters.name: width

setVisible.notes: Sets the element visible. When visible, elements update and render.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setWantKeyEvents.notes: Sets whether the element should receive keyboard events.

parameters.name: flag
parameters.notes: The flag to set.

setWidth.notes: Sets the width of the element on the screen. (In pixels)\n**NOTE**: If the element is set to stay on the screen, the width is capped.

parameters.name: width
parameters.notes: The width to set. (In pixels)

setWidthAndParentWidth.notes: Sets the width of the element and all parent elements up to their root element. (In pixels)

parameters.name: width
parameters.notes: The width to set. (In pixels)

setX.notes: Sets the x-coordinate of the element on the screen. (In pixels)\n**NOTE**: If the element is set to stay on the screen, the maximum x coordinate is capped.

parameters.name: x
parameters.notes: The x-coordinate to set. (In pixels)

setXScroll.notes: Sets the x-offset of the horizontal scrollbar and the contents of the scrollbar-pane. If the given value falls outside the range of the horizontal scrollbar and its contents, the value set will be clamped to the range.

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The value to set. (In pixels)

setY.notes: Sets the y-coordinate of the element on the screen. (In pixels)\n**NOTE**: If the element is set to stay on the screen, the maximum y coordinate is capped.

parameters.name: y
parameters.notes: The y-coordinate to set. (In pixels)

setYScroll.notes: Sets the y-offset of the vertical scrollbar and the contents of the scrollbar-pane. If the given value falls outside the range of the vertical scrollbar and its contents, the value set will be clamped to the range.

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The value to set. (In pixels)

shrinkX.notes: Shrinks the element's width by a given value.

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The value to shrink the width. (In pixels)

shrinkY.notes: Shrinks the element's height by a given value.

parameters.name: value
parameters.notes: The height to shrink. (In pixels)

stayOnSplitScreen.notes: Sets if the element stays on a split-screen for a player, clamping the element between the ranges for the player's screen-space.\n**NOTE**: If the amount of players is one, then the method does nothing.

parameters.name: playerIndex
parameters.notes: The player's index value. (between 0 and 3)

suspendStencil.notes: Suspends (or halts) the stencil used to clip render / draw calls from rendering outside the set box boundary of the element. Once suspended, anything drawn outside the boundary will show.

returns.notes: A formally-wrapped for **tostring(self)** using the** getUIName()** to formally name the printed result.

update.notes: Triggered every updated tick in the game's simulation.

updateScrollbars.notes: Updates the horizontal and vertical scrollbars, clamping the vertical scrollbar if outside of the content-range.

wrapInCollapsableWindow.notes: Wraps the element in a window class instance. (By Default **ISCollapsableWindow**)

parameters.name: title
parameters.notes: The title of the window.

parameters.name: isResizable
parameters.notes: True if the window can be resized by the player.

parameters.name: subClass
parameters.notes: If set, the class object is used instead. If nil, **ISCollapsableWindow** is used.

returns.notes: The instance of the wrapping class.
